==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sib
<hw>Sib</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Related by blood; akin.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your kindred is but . . . little <qex>sib</qex> to you.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[He] is no fairy birn, ne <qex>sib</qex> at all⟦br⟧
To elfs, but sprung of seed terrestrial.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sibbens</ent>⟦br⟧
